WEBVTT

00:11:59.135 --> 00:12:03.475
He gets ready, 
the ball is set, and he kicks.

00:12:03.475 --> 00:12:05.353
And the most amazing thing is,

00:12:05.353 --> 00:12:08.585
10 seconds after he did that,
and looked at us on the pitch,

00:12:08.585 --> 00:12:10.862
he told us, celebrating as you saw,

00:12:10.862 --> 00:12:12.692
"I felt the ball."

00:12:13.562 --> 00:12:15.759
And that's priceless.

00:12:15.759 --> 00:12:17.631
(Applause)

00:12:17.631 --> 00:12:19.131
So where is this going to go?

00:12:19.131 --> 00:12:21.066
I have two minutes to tell you

00:12:21.066 --> 00:12:24.316
that it's going to the limits
of your imagination.

00:12:24.316 --> 00:12:26.495
Brain-actuating technology is here.

00:12:26.495 --> 00:12:29.049
This is the latest: We just
published this a year ago,

00:12:29.049 --> 00:12:31.282
the first brain-to-brain interface